IMF’s Chopra Says Ireland Tackling Mortgage Arrears Sensibly

-- B y   F i n b a r r   F l y n n
-- 
2011-10-20T13:59:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/imf-s-chopra-says-ireland-tackling-mortgage-arrears-sensibly.html
International Monetary Fund Deputy
Director Ajai Chopra said that Ireland is going about resolving
mortgage arrears at its banks in a “sensible” way.   Chopra, speaking to reporters in Dublin on Ireland’s
quarterly bailout review, said the government is right to take a
“case-by-case” approach on mortgage arrears.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Finbarr Flynn at 
 fflynn3@bloomberg.net  